s to a fascinating and important voice in the history of modern Jewish ethics and spirituality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aEthicistszLithuaniaxPhilosophy. 0aJewish ethics. 0aMusar movementxHistory. 0aRabbiszLithuaniaxPhilosophy. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Philosophy. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Religious Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Jewish Studies. 4aJewish Studies : Judaica. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / History.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845836640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438458366423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438458366/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles